<div class="xar-mod-head">
    <span class="xar-mod-title">
        <xar:mlstring>Weather</xar:mlstring>
    </span>
</div>
<div class="xar-mod-body" style="display:block;">
    <h2><xar:mlstring>Overview</xar:mlstring></h2>
    
    <div style="border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: #B3B3B3; padding: 1px;">
        <div style="float: right; text-align:right; display:block;padding:10px;">
            <a href="http://www.weather.com"><img 
                src="modules/weather/xarimages/TWClogo_64px.png" border="0" 
                alt="weather.com&reg;" width="86" height="64" /></a>
        </div>
        <div class="xar-mod-title" style="margin-top: 1em; margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 15%; width: auto; border-width: 1px; border-color: #B3B3B3; border-style: none none dotted none;">
            <xar:mlstring>What is it?</xar:mlstring>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; text-align:left;">
            <em><xar:mlstring><strong>weather.com&reg;</strong> XML Data Feed</xar:mlstring></em><br />
            <ul>
                <li><xar:mlstring>Downloads the <strong>weather.com&reg;</strong> xml data feeds and presents your forecast.</xar:mlstring></li>
                <li><xar:mlstring>Implements the guidelines defined in the <strong>weather.com&reg;</strong> SDK.</xar:mlstring></li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <br />
        <div class="xar-mod-title" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; width: auto; border-width: 1px; border-color: #B3B3B3; border-style: none none dotted none;">
            <xar:mlstring>How to use it?</xar:mlstring>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; text-align:left;">
            <xar:mlstring>
                You need to register at <strong>weather.com&reg;</strong> in order to use this module.  This seems like
                a fair trade since you will be using their feeds and they do cover the entire planet.  Just follow the
                steps below and you should be up and running in no time.          
            </xar:mlstring>
            <ul>
                <li><xar:mlstring>Register for a <strong>Partner ID</strong> and <strong>License Key</strong> at </xar:mlstring><a href="http://www.weather.com/services/xmloap.html">http://www.weather.com/services/xmloap.html</a>.</li>
                <li><xar:mlstring>You'll receive an email with your <strong>Partner ID</strong> and <strong>License Key</strong>, along with some other information.</xar:mlstring></li>
                <li><xar:mlstring>Enter you <strong>Partner ID</strong> and <strong>License Key</strong> into the XoapWeather Config.</xar:mlstring></li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <br />
        <div class="xar-mod-title" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; width: auto; border-width: 1px; border-color: #B3B3B3; border-style: none none dotted none;">
            <xar:mlstring>Included Blocks</xar:mlstring>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; text-align:left;">
            <ul>
                <li><xar:mlstring>Current Conditions</xar:mlstring></li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <br />
        <div class="xar-accent" style="text-align: center; border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: #B3B3B3; padding: 0.5em 1em 0.5em 1em; margin-top: 5px;">
            <xar:mlstring>Extended information about this module can be found at</xar:mlstring> 
            <a href="http://xaraya.simiansynapse.com">http://xaraya.simiansynapse.com</a>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
